Hi @Frennetix!

Wow that must be a really old demo. I think what you want is to set either, or both,  the [`scroller_upAfterSort`](https://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/example-widget-scroller.html#scroller-up-after-sort) or [`scroller_jumpToHeader`](https://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/example-widget-scroller.html#scroller-jump-to-header) option to `false`.

```js
$("table.scroll, table#update").tablesorter({
  theme: 'blue',
  widgets: ["zebra", "filter", "scroller"],
  widgetOptions: {
    scroller_upAfterSort: false,
    scroller_jumpToHeader: false
  }
});
```

I've fixed the code in [that demo](http://jsfiddle.net/Mottie/s4ACj/32/), but it still scrolls a little, so I'm not sure if that'll solve the issue.

