I'd consider [the way django handles autoescaping](https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/1.10/ref/templates/builtins/#std:templatefilter-escape)

> Escapes a string’s HTML. Specifically, it makes these replacements:
< is converted to &lt;
> is converted to &gt;
' (single quote) is converted to &#39;
" (double quote) is converted to &quot;
& is converted to &amp;

This patch doesn't escape input; it urlencodes it. URL encoding should be applied to URL parameters. Not HTML content.

