Hi @RevolutionTech 
Is not possible to do `offer_count.invalidate(1)` because `offer_count` is a nested method in the instance method `has_offers`

I resolved in this manner (not so beauty but perfect for my purpose, because i don't want to invalidate group but instance method)

```
from django.core.cache import cache
from cache_utils.decorators import cached


class City(models.Model):
    # ... field declarations

    # an example how to cache django model methods by instance id
    def has_offers(self):
        @cached(60*60*24*30, 'offers_{0}'.format(self.pk)) #30 days
        def offer_count(pk):
            return self.offer_set.count()
        return offer_count(self.pk) > 0

    @classmethod
    def invalidate_offer_count(cls, pk)
        cache.invalidate_group('offers_{0}'.format(pk))
```

Hope it helps and i think this code could be inserted in the README to help other users

