Solution:
```python
class SomeSchema(ma.Schema):
    @ma.post_load(pass_many=True, pass_original=True)
    def __post_load(self, data, many, original_data):
        if hasattr(self.Meta, 'model'):
            if many:
                assert len(data) == len(original_data)
                for i in range(len(data)):
                    data[i]['_entity'] = original_data[i]  # here is your bind
                return tuple(self.Meta.model(**d) for d in data)
            else:
                data['_entity'] = original_data
                return self.Meta.model(**data)
        return maybe_attr_dict(data)
```

You can use the `include` class Meta option, like so:


```python
class MySchema(Schema):
   class Meta:
       include = {
            'name': fields.Str(attribute='_name', dump_only=True),
            'age': fields.Int(attribute='_age', load_only=True)
        }
```

