> The concern I had with Create Project as a classmethod of Project (if not folded into __init __) is that you'd have to create a project from a previously initialized project object containing its own token and url, which seems awkward at best.

That's not how [classmethods](http://stackoverflow.com/questions/12179271/python-classmethod-and-staticmethod-for-beginner) work. Here's the pseudocode:

```python

class Project(object):

    @classmethod
    def create_project(cls, url, token, details, **constructor_kwargs):
        response = make API call to create project with url, supertoken & details
        return cls(url, response['new token'], **constructor_kwargs)
    
    def __init__(self, url, token, other stuff...):
         main constructor stuff
```

