@lelit I'm sorry for being unclear. There's an issue with the tagged v1.1 release of rapidjson, where having both [patternProperties and additionalProperties set](https://github.com/Tencent/rapidjson/issues/825) causes a premature assertion.

This pattern is generally useful for describing series of observation data, where each series shares a common structure but the number of series is changing. 

For example, I've verified that the example pulled from the original bug is reproducible here.

```python
#!/usr/bin/env python3

import rapidjson as json

schema = json.dumps({
  "type": "object",
  "additionalProperties": False,
  "patternProperties": {
    "^i": { "type": "string" }
  }
})

test_data = json.dumps({"item": "hello"})

validate = json.Validator(schema)
validate(test_data)
```

This popular [guide to jsonschema v4](https://spacetelescope.github.io/understanding-json-schema/reference/object.html#pattern-properties) describes this use case where you may only be interested in patternProperties. 

I've actually verified that the bugfix works in this case and I've added a test case to exercise this issue.
